history.text: hello there
Hello! Have you ever seen The Wolf of Wall Street
No I have not. When did it come out?
It came out in 2013, and was directed by Martin Scorsese.
Ok, which actors are in it
Leonardo DiCaprio, Jonah Hill, Margot Robbie, Kyle Chandler, and Rob Reiner. It's amazing.
Oh wow I thought I had seen all of Leo's films. I like him  and Jonah hill the other actors I dont recognize. What is this film about?
It is about Leo's portrayal of Jordan Belfort. He was a stockbroker who engaged in fraud on Wall Street.
And what else happened?

Patrick Denham plays an FBI agent who tries to take him down. Matthew McConaughey always
 plays Jordan's mentor.
ok and is this a true story or fiction?
what happens to Leo?
This is a true story. It got a 7.8 On Rotten Tomatoes. He first takes a job in penny stocks where he uses an aggressive pitching style to gain a larger commission. Making himself a small fortune.
sounds like he got greedy
7.8 is not a good rateing
He certainly did. It really just started as a way to be able to pay his bills. 78% is still better than a failing grade! One of the better black comedy movies.
ok sorry thought it said 7.8
So did he have a family?
and what happened to make him commit fraud?
7.8 out of 10! During the movie Margot Robbie plays his wife, Naomi.
ok I get it now, yes that is an ok rateing
Does he have children?
His wife finds out about prostitutes and it doesn't go so well. Jordan illegally makes money by lying about information on stocks he is selling.
He does have a child during the movie
Oh No!
What happens to his family? His marriage?
When she finds out they divorce.
Oh so sad.
I wouldnt stick around either though with prostitutes and so on. Does he go to jail, do they catch  him?
Yes, but Jordan definitely has a very fun run of things up until he comes crashing down.
He tries to make a co-op deal with the feds, but slips a note to someone he is ratting on saying he is wearing a wire.
does he live the high life?
They  rat on him for ratting on wearing the wire, and he goes down with 3 years in prison.
so he could not even be honest then either...
Absolutely, with all that money and power he did whatever he wanted. Honesty is thrown out the window at that point.
